set {c1s3_old_ac_tried} = false
set {c1s3_animal_tried} = false
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	audio music "res://assets/audio/bg/suspicious.mp3" [loop="true"]
	[background arg="res://Bg/faculty_few.png" fade="1.5"]
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 1/C1s3/The_protagonist_enters.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist enters the school faculty room and observes several teachers and students engage in school work.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 1/C1s3/The_protagonist_sees.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist sees the Principal and approaches him.
	join Principal (Principal_half) right [animation="Instant In" length="0.0"]
	join Celestine (half) left [animation="Slide From Left"]
	Celestine: Excuse me Principal Alan, do you have time to talk sir?
	Principal: Classes are over, you should head home as soon as possible to stay out of trouble. However, students do have a right to ask their principal for advice.
	Principal: Fine, go ahead and ask me anything.
	Celestine: I'm just curious about the ruined exam papers. Is it true that they ruined to the point that they can't be graded?
	Principal: Yes, it's true. All of the exam papers of Grade 12-A are wet. Thankfully the exam papers of Grade 12-B  weren't included.
	Celestine: Can I take a look at the place where it happened sir?
	Principal: It was already cleaned up earlier, here take a look. I took a photo of the mess earlier since the store where the leaking air conditioner was bought didn't believe that it was leaking.
	leave --All--
	[background arg="res://Pics/Exam_ruined.png" fade="0.3"]
	"Celestine (Thinking)": Hmmm...... the water seems to be a bit too much from only a natural leak. The amount of water looks more like from a pipe instead of a leak.
	[background arg="res://Pics/Ac_leak.png" fade="0.3"]
	label Deduction_celestine
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 1/C1s3/Whats_wrong.mp3" volume="0.0"]
	What's wrong with this picture?
	- The airconditioning unit looks old so it was only natural that it leaked | [if {c1s3_old_ac_tried} == false]
		set {c1s3_old_ac_tried} = true
		[signal arg="wrong_choice"]
		jump Deduction_celestine
	- The tube is cut, but the door was locked. How did they get in?
		jump After_celestine
	- The tube where the leak is looks like it was bitten by an animal. | [if {c1s3_animal_tried} == false]
		set {c1s3_animal_tried} = true
		[signal arg="wrong_choice"]
		jump Deduction_celestine
	label After_celestine
	Celestine: Sir Alan, the tube was definitely cut. But there's no sign of forced entry on the door.
	Principal: That is impossible. Only the staff have keys to this room.
	[background arg="res://Bg/faculty_few.png" fade="0.0"]
	join Celestine (half) left [animation="Instant In" length="0.1"]
	join Principal right [animation="Instant In" length="0.1"]
	Celestine: Unless someone stole a key... or was given one.
	Principal: That implies deliberate sabotage from someone with access. Why would someone do this?
	Celestine: Considering that this incident made it so that the exam papers cannot be graded. The motive should be to cause a retake.
	Principal: And because they already took the exam, even though the exam questions will be altered. The exam will be much easier since we have a deadline to follow so we cant rigorously alter the exam questions.
	Celestine: Correct Sir
	Principal: As an educator this is unacceptable, but I can't really investigate this myself since the 3rd grading is ending and I have too much work to finish.
	Celestine: Can I investigate this in your stead sir?
	Principal: Are you sure? Is all your school work already done? If not then I can't let you ignore your responsibilities while you investigate this.
	Celestine: All my exams are already done and I have already passed all my requirements.
	Principal: Fine, you investigate this matter. I'll inform the staff and teachers to cooperate.
	Celestine: Leave it to me sir.
	Principal: Good.
	"Celestine (Thinking)": My phone is buzzing. It's a message from Mark.
	leave --All--
	[background arg="res://Pics/Mark_msg.jpg" fade="0.2"]
	# Placeholder for the picture Mark sent
	Celestine: He sent a picture? Wait a minute.
	Celestine: I don't have any mobile data left. How did I receive this photo?
	[background arg="res://Pics/Wifi_Faculty.png" fade="0.2"]
	Celestine: I'm connected to "Faculty_Wifi".
	"Celestine (Thinking)": That's strange, i don't remember connected to this network. What should i do?
	if {selected_subject} == "english":
		[signal arg="start_minigame wifi_router"]
	elif {selected_subject} == "math":
		Celestine: Two devices connected to the WiFi - at 8\:00 PM and 9\:00 PM.
		Celestine: If I use logical deduction to match devices to suspects...
		Celestine: I can systematically eliminate possibilities and identify who was here!
		[signal arg="start_minigame logic_grid_wifi_math"]
	elif {selected_subject} == "science":
		Celestine: Two WiFi connections logged - different times and signal strengths.
		Celestine: Using physics principles, I can analyze signal propagation patterns...
		Celestine: Signal strength follows the inverse square law - closer devices = stronger signals!
		[signal arg="start_minigame logic_grid_wifi_science"]
	[background arg="res://Bg/faculty_few.png" fade="0.0"]
	join Celestine (half) left
	Celestine: Sir, does this room have a dedicated Wi-Fi router?
	join Principal right
	Principal: Yes, since the general wifi set up for the school is weak in the faculty room. A dedicated wifi network and a router for staff use is installed here.
	Principal: While it may be for staff use, it is also intended for students to use it as well. Why?
	Celestine: My phone just auto-connected to it. If the culprit was here, their phone might have done the same. Can we check the connection logs?
	Principal: All the phones of the students should have access since it the password was provided in the orientation and is available to see at the bulletin board.
	Principal: That is a clever idea. Let me check the admin panel...
	leave --All--
	[background arg="res://Pics/Wifi_Logs.png" fade="0.2"]
	Principal: Interesting. Two devices connected to the "Faculty_Wifi" network yesterday evening.
	Principal: One connected at 8\:00 PM, device name "Galaxy_A52". The other at 9\:00 PM, device name "Redmi_Note_10".
	Celestine: Galaxy A52 and Redmi Note 10... Those are specific models.
	Celestine: Exactly. It's a significant addition to my clues.
	[signal arg="unlock_evidence wifi_logs_c1"]
	Celestine: I need to confirm who owns these.
	[background arg="res://Bg/faculty_few.png" fade="0.0"]
	join Principal right
	join Celestine left
	Celestine: (Texts Mark) "Hey, do you know anyone in 12-A who uses a Galaxy A52 or a Redmi Note 10?"
	Mark replies\: "I'm not sure about the specific models. But Alice, the class monitor, collects our phones during exams. She would know."
	Mark replies\: "She's usually at the lockers this time."
	Celestine: Thanks, Sir. I have a lead to follow up on.
	leave Principal
	leave Celestine [animation="Instant Out"]
	[background arg="res://Bg/hallway.png" fade="1.5"]
	join Celestine center
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 1/C1s3/The_protagonist_leaves.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist  leaves the room and is walking in the hallway
	join Celestine (half) left
	"Celestine (Thinking)": Of course the students of 12-A are definitely suspects but it's gonna take a long time to question them all individually, which makes it impossible to catch them before the grades are permanently recorded.
	"Celestine (Thinking)": It would also alert the perp which makes the investigation harder.
	"Celestine (Thinking)": Also it wouldn't be impossible for this to be coordinated by multiple people.
	Celestine: Ughhhh... This is so hard. Why did I think that I could do this.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 1/C1s3/The_protagonist_walks.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist  walks in the hallway to leave the building to go to the school gate
	leave Celestine
	# Celestine goes to find Alice (Placeholder: Janitor Fred)
	[background arg="res://Bg/school_gate.png" fade="1.5"]
	join Alice right [animation="Instant In" length="0.1"]
	join Celestine left [animation="Slide From Left" length="1.0"]
	Celestine: Excuse me... Alice?
	# Placeholder: Janitor Fred represents Alice, the class monitor
	Alice: Yes? What is it, Celestine?
	Celestine: Mark said you know a lot about our classmates' phones since you collect them. Do you know anyone who uses a Galaxy A52 or a Redmi Note 10?
	Alice: Hmm... let me think.
	Alice: Oh, right. Ben has a Galaxy A52. He's always bragging about the camera.
	Alice: And Greg has a Redmi Note 10. I remember the red case.
	Celestine: Thanks, Alice. That helps a lot.
	leave Alice [animation="Slide To Left"]
	"Celestine (Thinking)": So the devices in the logs belong to Ben and Greg. They were in the faculty room last night.
	"Celestine (Thinking)": I have the suspects. Now I just need to prove it.
	join "Diwata Laya" (Half_mirror) right
	[signal arg="laya_start"]
	"Diwata Laya": It's alright you can do this.
	[signal]
	Celestine: Looks like you're awake. I've narrowed it down to two students.
	"Diwata Laya": Last time, it took me too much energy so I had to rest. I've recovered mostly but the help I can give is limited.
	Celestine: This case is kinda rough though, I really need your help.
	"Diwata Laya": I've seen what's been happening even though I've been resting for a while. Don't worry too much, do what you can and we'll see how I can help. Since I've recovered quite a bit, my ability to compel people to tell the truth or cooperate has come back to me.
	Celestine: Well that's gonna be super helpful.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/Chapter 1/C1s3/Diwata_Laya_is_your_helper.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Diwata Laya is your helper! She is very intelligent and can help you quite a lot. However she is very limited as she is not allowed to interact much with the human world, so she is limited in the help she can give.
	Celestine: Great, I'll tell Mark what we've learned later. Help me brainstorm once we get home later.
	"Diwata Laya": Ok.
	[signal arg="laya_end"]
	leave --All-- [animation="Instant Out" length="0.0"]
	jump c1s4/
